{
  "mcpServers": {
    "agi-server": {
      "command": "node",
      "args": [
        "/path/to/your/AGI/mcp-server.js"
      ],
      "env": {},
      "description": "AGI server with persistent memory, reasoning, and reflection capabilities"
    }
  }
}

/* 
Setup Instructions:

1. Copy this file to claude_desktop_config.json in your Claude Desktop configuration directory
2. Update the path in "args" to point to your actual AGI directory:
   - Windows: "C:\\Users\\YourName\\Documents\\GitHub\\AGI\\mcp-server.js"
   - macOS/Linux: "/Users/YourName/Documents/GitHub/AGI/mcp-server.js"
3. Restart Claude Desktop
4. The AGI server will be available with memory, reasoning, and reflection capabilities

Default Claude Desktop config locations:
- Windows: %APPDATA%\Claude\claude_desktop_config.json
- macOS: ~/Library/Application Support/Claude/claude_desktop_config.json
- Linux: ~/.config/Claude/claude_desktop_config.json

The server provides these MCP tools:
- remember() - Store persistent memories
- recall() - Search stored memories
- reflect() - Meta-cognitive analysis
- reason() - Symbolic reasoning chains
- assess_confidence() - Evaluate statement certainty
*/